Exploratory analysis: Formal limits

Summary: The formal limits dimension is probably the least problematic of our dimensions.

The Formal limits scale in the summaries below has been constructed on the basis of these items:

  • 35 Does the proposal have to be submitted as a (draft) legal text?

  • 37 Is there a clarity of the question requirement?

  • 38 Is there a unity of form requirement?

  • 39 Is there a unity of substance requirement?

Important Note: for the Law-initiated, item 35 was not used.

A quick glimpse at the distribution of Answers (Yes vs No) per item suggests that most items elicited a good number of Yes responses.

Answer 35 37 38 39
No 72 85 131 108
Yes 40 54 8 31

The one potentially problematic cell is related to item 38 (unity of form). This is a very rare requirement. It is only relevant in 4 countries as shown in table below

Country Instrument
Italy Rejective initiative
Italy Subnational-initiated
Liechtenstein Proactive initiative
Liechtenstein Rejective initiative
Liechtenstein Subnational-initiated
Lithuania Legislature-initiated
Lithuania Proactive initiative
Switzerland Proactive initiative

Leaving aside any issues related to item 38 for the time being, the analytical summaries below contain 2 types of summary for the Formal limits, a) a graphical summary and b) table summaries with all the cases per instrument (see Annex for detailed country/item/instrument lists).
